“Dear Women, Hire a cook if you can, Hire a Nanny if you can, if you can get a Driver, please get one! Your womanhood should not be about suffering, Normalise luxury in your life, Preserve yourself 💕” A quote from my favourite @priyankachopra that I had shared few days back and sooo many women resonated with this because somewhere in the past, women have been taught that they can be multitaskers and can do it all by themselves for the “betterment” of the family.. and those women are still waiting for their awards and crowns 👑 (pun intended;) 

No offence to those who are home makers, love doing the chores and cook for their families.. but those who are working or those who can afford a little bit help but not doing because that’s how it’s done in their families, please speak up for yourself 🙌 This investment especially in a country like India, where most people can afford, can bring happiness, peace in families..and of course you use that time and energy to say yes to more opportunities, quality time for your family, me time and so much more 💕

latestPosts.caption:
Okay, no matter how much we say i know having stretch marks can make women very conscious & less confident about their bodies & that’s completely okay.. 💁🏼‍♀️
however, don’t let that stop you from wearing what you love.. you do get used to them eventually. 🤗

Can we remove stretch marks? 
Unfortunately, not completely ! No amount of creams or oils can help you get rid of stretch marks completely. There are treatments available like lazer skin resurfacing & dermabrasion etc but not sure how effective they are. 

Key is to prevent them -

1. If you gain & loose weight rapidly, you’re bound to have them. 
2. Start early, i asked my doc to write me a prescription as early as second month. Because once your tummy grows, then there’s no point. You have to keep it hydrated & moisturised and eat food that improves skin’s elasticity. 
3. I used to apply doc recommended cream in the morning & massage my tummy with bio oil at night (not sponsored:) 
Pro Tip - Damp your skin before you apply for best results. 

Having said & done, genetics play a major role, if your mom had them- chances are you might too 😅 mine didnt 😛 

Shoot all your ques in the comments 🫶🏻

Moms often ask me or other moms if they should plan another baby but really they should ask THEMSELVES these following questions before planning 👇🏼

1. Are you financially capable of raising two children comfortably? 
2. Are you mentally prepared for doing it all over again? 
3. Do you have enough support system or you’re confident you can raise two children on your own? 
4. Does your partner want it? 
5. Is your marriage healthy & sound enough or it has loose ends? This you should ask before planning any baby actually because a child doesn’t really strengthen a marriage (sorry to bust that bubble)  in-fact it puts it through even more tests. 
6. Are you physically healthy enough to be going through pregnancy,labour & breastfeeding again ? 

Yes, our parents or for that matter many parents figure it out but we aren’t living in the same simpler times. If you & your partner really want to have a baby then of course you’ll figure it out but if you have doubts, then it’s better to ask yourself these questions before planning. 

The point is that your decision shouldn’t be influenced by what other people feel is right because there’s no right or wrong here, it’s really about how you feel about raising children 🤗

I used to think i need to try different exercises, some thing new to keep it fun & effective but i learnt that keeping it simple & following the same routine at least for 6 to 12 months was the key to actually see results. So don’t waste your time trying fancy new exercises..💁🏼‍♀️
